<p>â¢ <a href="/wiki/Northern_Ireland_Civil_Rights_Association" title="Northern Ireland Civil Rights Association">Northern Ireland Civil Rights Association</a> formed (1967)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_the_Bogside" title="Battle of the Bogside">Battle of the Bogside</a> (1969)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Northern_Ireland_riots_of_August_1969" title="Northern Ireland riots of August 1969" class="mw-redirect">Riots across Northern Ireland</a> (1969)<br />
â¢ Beginning of <a href="/wiki/Operation_Banner" title="Operation Banner">Operation Banner</a> (1969)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Social_Democratic_and_Labour_Party" title="Social Democratic and Labour Party">Social Democratic and Labour Party</a> formed (1970)<br />
â¢ Internment without trial begins with <a href="/wiki/Operation_Demetrius" title="Operation Demetrius">Operation Demetrius</a> (1971)<br />
â¢ <strong class="selflink">Bloody Sunday</strong> by <a href="/wiki/British_Army" title="British Army">British Army</a> (1972)<br />
â¢ Northern Ireland government dissolved. Direct rule from London begins (1972)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Bloody_Friday_(1972)" title="Bloody Friday (1972)">Bloody Friday</a> by Provisional IRA (1972)<br />
â¢ Power sharing <a href="/wiki/Northern_Ireland_Assembly_(1973)" title="Northern Ireland Assembly (1973)">Northern Ireland Assembly</a> set up with SDLP and <a href="/wiki/Ulster_Unionist_Party" title="Ulster Unionist Party">Ulster Unionist Party</a> in power (1973)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Ulster_Workers_Council" title="Ulster Workers Council" class="mw-redirect">Ulster Workers Council</a> strike ends power sharing <a href="/wiki/Northern_Ireland_Assembly_(1973)" title="Northern Ireland Assembly (1973)">Northern Ireland Assembly</a> (1974)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Dublin_and_Monaghan_bombings" title="Dublin and Monaghan bombings">Dublin and Monaghan bombings</a> by <a href="/wiki/Ulster_Volunteer_Force" title="Ulster Volunteer Force">UVF</a> with alleged British Army assistance (1974)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Kingsmill_massacre" title="Kingsmill massacre">Kingsmill massacre</a> by South Armagh Republican Action Force (1976)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Warrenpoint_Ambush" title="Warrenpoint Ambush" class="mw-redirect">Warrenpoint Ambush</a> by Provisional IRA (1979)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/1981_Irish_hunger_strike" title="1981 Irish hunger strike">1981 Irish hunger strike</a> by Provisional IRA and <a href="/wiki/Irish_National_Liberation_Army" title="Irish National Liberation Army">INLA</a> members (1981)<br />
â¢ Hunger striker <a href="/wiki/Bobby_Sands" title="Bobby Sands">Bobby Sands</a> elected MP. Marks turning point as <a href="/wiki/Sinn_F%C3%A9in" title="Sinn FÃ©in">Sinn FÃ©in</a> begins to move towards electoral politics (1981)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Maze_Prison_escape" title="Maze Prison escape">Maze Prison escape</a>. 38 Provisional IRA prisoners escape from H-Block 7 of <a href="/wiki/HM_Prison_Maze" title="HM Prison Maze" class="mw-redirect">HM Prison Maze</a> (1983)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Anglo-Irish_Agreement" title="Anglo-Irish Agreement">Anglo-Irish Agreement</a> between British and Irish governments (1985)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Remembrance_Day_bombing" title="Remembrance Day bombing">Remembrance Day bombing</a> by Provisional IRA (1987)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Northern_Ireland_peace_process" title="Northern Ireland peace process">Peace Process</a> begins (1988)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Operation_Flavius" title="Operation Flavius">Operation Flavius</a>-<a href="/wiki/Milltown_Massacre" title="Milltown Massacre" class="mw-redirect">Milltown Massacre</a>-<a href="/wiki/Corporals_killings" title="Corporals killings">Corporals killings</a> sequence of violence (1988)<br />
â¢ First Provisional IRA ceasefire (1994)<br />
â¢ Loyalist ceasefire (1994)<br />
â¢ Second Provisional IRA ceasefire (1997)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Belfast_Agreement" title="Belfast Agreement">Belfast Agreement</a> (1998) signals the end of the Troubles<br />
â¢ Assembly elections held, with SDLP and UUP winning most seats (1998)<br />
â¢ <a href="/wiki/Omagh_bombing" title="Omagh bombing">Omagh bombing</a> by dissident <a href="/wiki/Real_IRA" title="Real IRA" class="mw-redirect">Real IRA</a> (1998)<br /></p>
